      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <2% change in QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) between the production mesh and a uniformly refined mesh at 1.5× element density.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the non-cannulated screw construct. Stiffness changed 0.9%, yield force 1.4%, force at 40 mm 1.1% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation GCI < 1.5% for all QoIs. Production mesh selected at medium density. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
